    "Q1. Explain GET and POST methods.\n",
    "---> GET and POST are two commonly used methods in HTTP (Hypertext Transfer Protocol), which is the underlying protocol used for communication between web browsers and web servers. Both methods are used to send data from the client (usually a web browser) to the server, but they have different characteristics and purposes.\n",
    "GET is used for sennding the data through URL\n",
    "and post is used for sending the data through body post methods is secure then get method becuse in post information is hide."
   ]
  },
